Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:18.02,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fscx97.43\fscy86\shad0\fnBoopee\c&H646362&\bord10\fs21\frz350\pos(296.256,314)\3c&HF1EFF0&\clip(m 260.625 286 l 256 306 334.25 319 337.625 300)}for Mechazawa
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:18.07,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fscx97.43\fscy86\shad0\fnBoopee\c&H646362&\bord10\fs21\frz350\pos(296.37,313.9)\3c&HF1EFF0&\clip(m 260.625 286 l 256 306 334.25 319 337.625 300)}for Mechazawa
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:22.11,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fscx97.43\fscy86\shad0\fnBoopee\c&H646362&\bord10\fs21\frz350\pos(296.483,313.8)\3c&HF1EFF0&\clip(m 260.625 286 l 256 306 334.25 319 337.625 300)}for Mechazawa
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.90,0:04:20.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,OS 5.02 for Mechazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.40,0:04:21.44,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,OS?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.40,0:04:23.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What's OS?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:26.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, how should I explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.03,0:04:28.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In short, it's an operating system for computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.91,0:04:30.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,An operating system?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:34.12,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For example, suppose there is a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.12,0:04:40.05,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But if you don't educate this person,\Nhe can't speak, nor work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:44.22,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Similarly, computers\N will refuse to run without an OS.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.22,0:04:48.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In short, an OS is something that provides\Nthe computer's basic operating abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:51.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's quite a serious matter, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:55.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yes. Since it's a very serious matter,\NI'd like you to listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:04:59.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But it's about computers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:01.11,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mechazawa is different from computers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.90,0:05:04.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know how to answer that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:06.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,so why don't we go see\NMechazawa for the time being?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.62,0:05:09.58,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\shad0\bord0\c&H4C1627&\fnArial\fs26\frx30\fry332\org(454,204)\pos(431.639,247)\frz21.41}Library
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:12.08,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnAnna\shad0\c&H1F2732&\3c&H3E4877&\bord2\be2\frx40\fry16\frz275.372\t(\fs23)\move(30.589,360,128.019,315,0,2425)}Goethe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.70,0:05:15.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's agonizing about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:17.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's just that, since he's the type whose\Nexpression doesn't change with his emotions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:19.00,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,it's hard to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.63,0:05:25.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Maybe it'd be better to upgrade this\NOS thing to the latest one after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:26.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:34.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,With computers, installing a newer OS\Nonto an old model can cause a malfunction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:40.11,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Also, it's possible that you won't be able\Nto use your current printer any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:42.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That doesn't have anything\Nto do with Mechazawa, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:44.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Even I could tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:49.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In any case, he'll be a new Mechazawa\Nwho's different from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.95,0:05:52.03,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's how upgrading is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.70,0:05:55.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So there are various risks involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.58,0:05:58.50,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see. Well, in any case,\Nwhy don't we ask Mechazawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:01.84,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mechazawa, you look bummed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:03.67,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.67,0:06:06.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I've fallen in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:08.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Love?! With who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.80,0:06:15.39,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But there's no way a lowlife badass\Nlike me can pursue love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:18.69,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But realizing that doesn't stop this heartache.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.48,0:06:25.90,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If I could, I'd like to have a fresh start\Nand become a new person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:29.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's what I've been thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.32,0:06:32.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You wanna become a new person?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.45,0:06:36.25,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see. If that's the case, there's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.25,0:06:38.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mechazawa, we'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:42.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hold still for a bit. It'll only take a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.38,0:06:46.46,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Is it gonna be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.46,0:06:48.05,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It seems like it'll be all right somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.80,0:06:56.60,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord40\shad0\pos(362.532,300)\fs42\clip(85,80,629,325)\3c&H2D2D2D&}Warning\N\N\N{\fs28}If you continue, all previous\N\N data will be deleted.\N\NWould you like to continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.80,0:06:56.60,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\bord29\shad0\pos(241.31,385)\c&H243422&\3c&H02CA00&\fs36\clip(176.315,344.8,306.09,386.4)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.80,0:06:56.60,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord35\shad0\blur0.4\pos(487.152,385)\3c&H2E2D2F&\fs36\clip(418,348,553,387)}{}No
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.30,0:06:56.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If you continue,\N all previous data will be deleted?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.89,0:06:58.64,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, this isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.64,0:07:01.77,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It'd be better to stop for now and\Nread the manual one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:02.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:06.90,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He himself wants to have a fresh start.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:09.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So it'd be preferable if we delete\N everything without leaving any trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.40,0:07:10.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.20,0:07:13.41,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord25\shad0\pos(362.532,242)\fs36\3c&H2D2D2D&\clip(173,146,549,266)}Please enter the serial number.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.11,0:07:13.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What's a serial number?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.78,0:07:17.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's a password to prevent\N illegal use of the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.58,0:07:19.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But I can't find the number.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.21,0:07:23.00,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's not on the CD case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.71,0:07:28.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For name brands, normally a sticker\Ncan be found on the chassis, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.26,0:07:31.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Kamiyama, could this be it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:34.26,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:37.72,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Now, all I have to do is to enter\Nthe country name, region name,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.72,0:07:39.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,department name, date and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:40.52,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\alpha90\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord15\shad0\fs20\3c&H111111&\frx2\fry15\org(340,-4)\pos(369.329,243)\clip(m 216.375 243 l 215.25 275 330.75 261 382.875 251 490.5 225 492.875 189 360.25 221)}{\frz-2.5}In{\frz-1.8}st{\frz-1.4}al{\frz-0.9}la{\frz-0.5}ti{\frz-0.1}on{\frz0.5} co{\frz0.9}mp{\frz1.1}le{\frz1.4}te
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:40.56,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\alpha80\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord15\shad0\fs20\3c&H111111&\frx2\fry15\org(340,-4)\pos(369.329,243)\clip(m 216.375 243 l 215.25 275 330.75 261 382.875 251 490.5 225 492.875 189 360.25 221)}{\frz-2.5}In{\frz-1.8}st{\frz-1.4}al{\frz-0.9}la{\frz-0.5}ti{\frz-0.1}on{\frz0.5} co{\frz0.9}mp{\frz1.1}le{\frz1.4}te
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:40.60,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\alpha50\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord15\shad0\fs20\3c&H111111&\frx2\fry15\org(340,-4)\pos(369.329,243)\clip(m 216.375 243 l 215.25 275 330.75 261 382.875 251 490.5 225 492.875 189 360.25 221)}{\frz-2.5}In{\frz-1.8}st{\frz-1.4}al{\frz-0.9}la{\frz-0.5}ti{\frz-0.1}on{\frz0.5} co{\frz0.9}mp{\frz1.1}le{\frz1.4}te
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:41.23,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnPerfect DOS VGA 437\c&H08C407&\bord15\shad0\fs20\3c&H111111&\frx2\fry15\org(340,-4)\pos(369.329,243)\clip(m 216.375 243 l 215.25 275 330.75 261 382.875 251 490.5 225 492.875 189 360.25 221)}{\frz-2.5}In{\frz-1.8}st{\frz-1.4}al{\frz-0.9}la{\frz-0.5}ti{\frz-0.1}on{\frz0.5} co{\frz0.9}mp{\frz1.1}le{\frz1.4}te
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:44.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mechazawa responded!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.40,0:07:46.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Was the installation successful?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.61,0:07:47.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Good, it's successful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:48.44,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fs26\fnAnna\c&H724D47&\3c&HFFFFFF&\bord3\shad0\move(593.646,58,484.886,58,100,649)}Welcome to\N Internet Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.44,0:07:52.45,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fs26\fnAnna\c&H724D47&\3c&HFFFFFF&\bord3\shad0\pos(484.886,58)}Welcome to\N Internet Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:48.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Internet Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.94,0:07:50.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's successfully connected to the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.11,0:07:52.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.95,0:07:55.07,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But that's not the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.07,0:07:56.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.45,0:07:58.29,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh? Maeda?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:07:59.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.33,0:08:00.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:04.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,My name is Takeshi Hokuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.75,0:08:08.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm the heir to the Hokuto Foundation\Nand the next leader of the Hokuto Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.34,0:08:12.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm the man who was born\N and chosen to rule the masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.43,0:08:17.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! I've got the body of a seal!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:17.89,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\be2\pos(358,392)}Takeshi Hokuto (16)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.89,0:08:21.39,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why the heck has something like this happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.39,0:08:24.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No, calm down! Think calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:28.11,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Let me see, first, last night,\NI ate dinner at home and watched TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:32.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Like it's possible to think calmly\Nin this kind of situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:35.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, morning, Hokuto!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:38.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! That guy is me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:40.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Okay, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:44.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That seal's body has been switched with mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.21,0:08:45.71,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How can this be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.71,0:08:50.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,A supernatural phenomenon beyond\Nscientific explanation must have happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.21,0:08:53.47,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,As a first step, I need to tell this fact to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.84,0:08:57.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Shut up, you stupid seal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:08.02,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I-It was a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:10.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Are you awake, Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:11.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you, Jeeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:14.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:15.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.28,0:09:20.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know, since\Nsomeone else greeted them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.53,0:09:21.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hokuto!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.54,0:09:23.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Something serious has happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:24.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.00,0:09:26.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:28.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:31.17,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It has been a while since I saw you last.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.17,0:09:33.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, please pardon me for being a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:37.84,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you again. Are you two really unrelated?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.14,0:09:40.55,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are completely unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.55,0:09:43.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We have no connection whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:46.64,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,By the way, what is this\N serious thing you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:50.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.90,0:09:53.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I was so surprised, I forgot what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:54.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:57.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Have you had breakfast, Mr. Hayashida?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:10:00.24,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If you would like, why not\Nhave breakfast together?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.24,0:10:03.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's good timing!\NI'll accept your hospitality,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:05.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,since I haven't eaten anything\Nsince this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:07.67,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's morning right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.42,0:10:11.71,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.71,0:10:14.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You eat this luxuriously even in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:16.30,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Be quiet! Shut up and eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:20.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm so full!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:23.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Can I lay down on the couch a little bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:26.10,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So what's this serious thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.39,0:10:29.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Let's see... What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:30.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What did you come here for, bastard?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.44,0:10:34.86,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh! I remember it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.86,0:10:37.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's okay. It's not much\Nof a big deal anyway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.11,0:10:40.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There's something attached to Mechazawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:41.24,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.16,0:10:45.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\fnLeviBrush\fs72\c&H131313&\bord0\pos(262.835,439)}To Be Continued
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.95,0:10:44.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What happens next will be revealed\Nat the end of the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:45.01,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\alpha130\fs24\fnNeon\bord0\c&H4E1728&\blur0.5\pos(346.671,139)}Next\N\N\N\NEpisode
Dialogue: 1,0:11:45.01,0:11:50.02,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fs26\blur0.5\fnArial Black\bord3\c&H000000&\3c&HFBFAFC&\pos(192.595,50)}Sakigake!!\NCromartie High School
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.01,0:11:50.02,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fs26\blur0.6\fnArial Black\bord3.2\c&H000000&\3c&H3F3F3F&\pos(192.595,50)}Sakigake!!\NCromartie High School
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.01,0:11:50.02,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fnArial Black\shad0\fs36\bord2.2\blur0.5\c&HFCFCFE&\pos(481.487,390)}There's nothing more to be\N continued in this episode
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.59,0:11:37.17,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Dear Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:39.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Sakigake!! Cromartie High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.21,0:11:41.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Even though I'm speaking right now,
